This study investigates quantum system behaviors through computational physics methods. Our research leverages two complementary data sources: a comprehensive quantum computing simulator platform, accessible through quantum-sim.org, which enables extensive theoretical explorations, alongside private experimental error rate measurements obtained from our laboratory's quantum computing infrastructure (quantum-lab.org/data). The computational methodology enables us to analyze quantum mechanical phenomena under controlled conditions, comparing simulated predictions with real-world observations. This approach facilitates the investigation of quantum systems across various parameter spaces and environmental conditions, while maintaining precise control over system variables.
